      "content": "Sudafed is a decongestant that can be dangerous for a developing fetus, so you should not take it. Instead, I recommend a high dose of saline nasal spray combined with a steam inhalation to clear your sinuses safely. For severe congestion, you can also try sleeping with your head elevated and using a humidifier to keep your airways moist. If you continue to experience severe symptoms, please consult your obstetrician immediately for safe medical treatment.",
